text:
The wanton soup is nice, rest of stalls were not open when i went there at 5+pm.
Had the western food as well, sausage was so so but fries was freshly cooked and crispy!

Found this gem of a hawker center. Good breakfast selection and good choice of drinks stalls like teh tarik and old school breakfast like Chee Cheong Fun, Economic bee hoon and famous “Only One -Laksa”. Next to the hawker there is a Tanglin Halt roti prata looking good too. Parking is limited. Was attracted here by the old school peanut cake but they only open selected day. Better luck next time.

A true little gem of the west. A place to go for breakfast and be sure to be there early with lots of queuing if you wanna try the peanut pancake and the laksa. Pancake for me was really worth the queue but the laksa gravy was not thick enough for my liking. The lor mee has no queue and I think its pretty worth a try. Chee cheong fun was OK and average.
Nice nostalgic neighbourhood with many good food choices.  Alas, the estate is slated for demolition soon and most stalls will be closed nearing late 2019/2020. Go there when its still opened.

Unfortunately, I arrive at this market after 1pm and most of the stall have closed by now.. Definitely will come back next time in tbe morning to try out their famous Ming Jiang Kueh (peanut pancake) and duck noodle.
